Mauritius Gross Tourism Revenue Increases 7.6% on Arrivals

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-08-18T09:20:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-18/mauritius-gross-tourism-receipts-increased-7-6-in-first-half-agency-says.html
Mauritius’s gross tourism revenue
increased an annual 7.6 percent in the first six months of the
year, according to the Indian Ocean island nation’s  Central
Statistics Office .  Receipts increased to 21.3 billion rupees ($760 million)
from 19.8 billion rupees, the statistics agency said in a  report 
on its website today, citing data from the central bank.  Arrivals rose 5.8 percent to 464,604, led by Europeans, the
data agency said.  Tourism, along with textiles, is the nation’s main source
of foreign currency. Revenue for 2011 is expected to increase
7.7 percent to 42.5 billion rupees, according to the statistics
office, with the number of visitors growing 4.8 percent to
980,000.  Mauritius had 111 hotels in operation as end of June.  New
Mauritius Hotels Ltd. (NMH) , Sun Resorts Ltd. and Naiade Resorts Ltd.
are the largest leisure operators by market value.  To contact the reporter on this story:
